        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 10 at 6:21PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 621 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles north of Marshall, or 6 miles northeast of Hot Springs, moving
east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Faust, Allenstand, Mars Hill, and Wolf Ridge.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
